25. API Architecture
25.1 API Design Philosophy

The platform follows an API-First Architecture, ensuring all frontend interactions occur through versioned REST APIs. Every endpoint is designed to be:

Stateless
Idempotent (where applicable)
Secure
Versioned
Documented using OpenAPI (Swagger)
25.2 API Standards

Base URL

/api/v1
Response Format
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Analysis completed successfully.",
  "data": {},
  "metadata": {
    "requestId": "req_12345",
    "executionTime": "12.4s"
  }
}
Error Format
{
  "success": false,
  "error": {
    "code": "GITHUB_RATE_LIMIT",
    "message": "GitHub API rate limit exceeded."
  }
}
